<subSubSection id="E9ED3EED8C6DFFA6FF421CD31FFBC773" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="A1486D668C6DFFA6FF421CD31E3BC5B0" blockId="4.[175,1005,1496,1570]" lastBlockId="5.[148,978,194,1570]" lastPageId="5" lastPageNumber="52" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6DFFA7FF421CD31C6CC19B" bold="true" box="[199,303,1496,1517]" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Species large, robust (female 
<quantity id="660FC0838C6DFFA7FDDA1CD31F8AC19B" box="[607,713,1496,1517]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.85" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.7" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="18.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="17.0">17–20 mm</quantity>
long, male 
<quantity id="660FC0838C6DFFA7FCC71CD31EE8C19B" box="[834,939,1496,1517]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="4" pageNumber="51" unit="mm" value="16.0" valueMax="17.0" valueMin="15.0">15–17 mm</quantity>
long). 
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6DFFA7FF2A1CF81DA5C27E" box="[175,230,1523,1544]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Color</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation id="39CC71E38C6DFFA7FF731CF81C73C27E" box="[246,304,1523,1544]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="2.[197,228,837,856]" captionTargetBox="[418,761,197,810]" captionTargetId="figure-391@2.[417,762,194,816]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Fig. 1. Trichaptus mutillarius (Perty), female, dorsal habitus. Scale 1 mm." pageId="4" pageNumber="51">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
): Dorsum of head, pronotum, elytra and antennae black, except narrow areas near the base of pronotum and around scutellum and sixteen yellowish and reddish elytral maculae. One pair of round, large, reddish maculae on sides of anterior half, from intervals 4 to 8; 4 pairs of yellowish maculae distributed along midline from base to apex, close to suture, from intervals 1 to 3 or 1 to 4; 3 pairs of yellowish maculae on sides of elytra, the former on humeri and the other two behind the reddish maculae, from intervals 5 to 9 or 6 to 9. 
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FD9218261F2FC534" box="[535,620,301,322]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Vestiture</emphasis>
: Black areas covered with long, fine, erect, setae; reddish maculae covered with lanceolate imbricate scales and lacking setae; yellowish maculae with vestiture of elongate, partially overlapped scales and long, erect setae; vestiture of venter similar to that of yellowish maculae, but with more sparse scales; legs covered with long, erect, yellowish setae. Other morphological features of females and males as those described for the genus (
<figureCitation id="39CC71E38C6CFFA6FC8718BA1E2EC5B0" box="[770,877,433,454]" captionStart-0="Figs" captionStart-1="Figs" captionStartId-0="3.[169,208,886,905]" captionStartId-1="4.[197,236,727,746]" captionTargetBox-0="[149,980,195,865]" captionTargetBox-1="[185,994,194,706]" captionTargetId-0="figure-258@3.[148,980,194,865]" captionTargetId-1="figure-285@4.[184,995,194,706]" captionTargetPageId-0="3" captionTargetPageId-1="4" captionText-0="Figs. 2–8. Trichaptus mutillarius (Perty), female. 2) Head and rostrum, frontal view; 3) lateral view; 4) prementum, external view; 5) internal view; 6) left maxila; 7) right antennae; 8) abdominal ventrites. Scales figures 2–3, 7–8, 1 mm; figures 4–6, 0.5 mm." captionText-1="Figs. 9–15. Trichaptus mutillarius (Perty), genitalia. Female. 9) Sternite VIII; 10) ovipositor, lateral view; 11–12) spermathecae. Male. 13) Tergite VIII, sternites VIII and IX, spiculum gastale of male; 14) aedeagus with tegmen, ventral view; 15) aedeagus with endophallic structure, lateral view. Scales figures 9–10, 13–15, 1 mm; figures 11–12, 0.25 mm." pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Figs. 2–15</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1486D668C6CFFA6FF2918C71E91C647" blockId="5.[148,978,194,1570]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FF2918C71C36C597" bold="true" box="[172,373,460,481]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Note on Synonymy.</emphasis>
Perty (1832) gave a short description of 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FC8E18C71E92C597" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1832" box="[779,977,460,481]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Rhigus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmosarius">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FC8E18C71E92C597" box="[779,977,460,481]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Rhigus myrmosarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FF3B18EC1C00C58A" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1832" box="[190,323,487,508]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Rhigus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutillarius">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FF3B18EC1C00C58A" box="[190,323,487,508]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">R. mutillarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, based on different specimens from 
<collectingRegion id="6333A3848C6CFFA6FD2E18EC1E6CC58A" box="[683,815,487,508]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="D9E02DF68C6CFFA6FCBF18EC1E34C58A" box="[826,887,487,508]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Brazil</collectingCountry>
. In those descriptions the former is larger than the latter and has slight differences in color pattern. We suspect that they would correspond to the female and male of the species.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1486D668C6CFFA6FF291B3D1CDCC6ED" blockId="5.[148,978,194,1570]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FF291B3D1C10C63D" author="Boheman" box="[172,339,566,587]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref3956" refString="Boheman, C. H. 1833 - 1845. In: Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae (C. J. Schoenherr). Roret, Paris, Fleischer, Lipsiae. Vols. 1 - 8." type="book chapter" year="1833">Boheman (1833)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FE431B3D1F13C63D" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1833" box="[454,592,566,587]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cyphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linnei">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FE431B3D1F13C63D" box="[454,592,566,587]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Cyphus linnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
indicating that it was a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FF111B5A1CF5C610" authority="Germar" authorityName="Germar" box="[148,438,593,614]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trichaptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutillarius">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FF111B5A1C2BC610" box="[148,360,593,614]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Trichaptus mutillarius</emphasis>
Germar
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FE3E1B5A1F53C610" box="[443,528,593,614]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">in litteris</emphasis>
, but ignoring that this species had been already described by Perty (1832). 
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FE181B601F13C6F6" author="Schoenherr" box="[413,592,619,640]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 474" refId="ref4707" refString="Schoenherr, C. J. 1840. Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Roret, Paris, Fleischer, Lipsiae. Vol. 6, pt. 1, pp. I, 1 - 474." type="journal article" year="1840">Schoenherr (1840)</bibRefCitation>
also referred to these species but using the name 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FF711B8D1C10C6ED" box="[244,339,646,667]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cyphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linnaei">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FF711B8D1C10C6ED" box="[244,339,646,667]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">C. linnaei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(error).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A1486D668C6CFFA6FF291BAA1FFBC773" blockId="5.[148,978,194,1570]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FF291BAA1C74C6C0" author="Pascoe" box="[172,311,673,694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="419 - 428" refId="ref4534" refString="Pascoe, F. P. 1880. New neotropical Curculionidae. Part 1. Annals and Magazine of Natural History Ser. 5 5: 419 - 428." type="journal article" year="1880">Pascoe (1880)</bibRefCitation>
described 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FE221BAA1F4DC6C0" box="[423,526,673,694]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Trichaptus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FE221BAA1F4DC6C0" box="[423,526,673,694]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Trichaptus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, designating 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FD131BAA1E72C6C0" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1832" box="[662,817,673,694]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Rhigus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="myrmosarius">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FD131BAA1E72C6C0" box="[662,817,673,694]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">R. myrmosarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as 
<typeStatus id="7E4CD3C48C6CFFA6FCDC1BAA1EC1C6C0" box="[857,898,673,694]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">type</typeStatus>
species (pag. 420) and indicating that it is a synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FDE61BB01FF6C6A6" authorityName="Boheman" authorityYear="1833" box="[611,693,699,720]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Cyphus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="linnei">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FDE61BB01FF6C6A6" box="[611,693,699,720]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">C. linnei</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(pag. 422). The synonymy of the three species mentioned above was established in the catalog by 
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FCAF1BDD1D96C773" author="Dalla Torre" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 132" refId="ref4112" refString="Dalla Torre, K. W. Von, M. van Emden, and F. I. van Emden. 1936. Coleopterorum catalogus. Junk's Gravenhage. Pars 147, Curculionidae: Brachyderinae I, pp 1 - 132." type="book chapter" year="1936">
Dalla Torre 
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FC251BDD1E91C69D" box="[928,978,726,747]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">et al.</emphasis>
(1936)
</bibRefCitation>
, and has been reiterated in subsequent checklists.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E9ED3EED8C6CFFA5FF291A011F98C6F6" lastPageId="6" lastPageNumber="53" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph id="A1486D668C6CFFA6FF291A011FDCC079" blockId="5.[148,978,194,1570]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FF291A011CDEC769" bold="true" box="[172,413,778,799]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Type Material Studied.</emphasis>
Two females and 
<specimenCount id="B7F1A6EF8C6CFFA6FDDC1A001FF2C756" box="[601,689,779,800]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry id="D9E02DF68C6CFFA6FD6A1A001E68C756" box="[751,811,779,800]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, with type labels 
<taxonomicName id="66F716E58C6CFFA6FF111A2E1C07C74C" authorityName="Perty" authorityYear="1832" box="[148,324,805,826]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Rhigus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutillarius">
<emphasis id="9383B1748C6CFFA6FF111A2E1C07C74C" box="[148,324,805,826]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Rhigus mutillarius</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, of the type collection of the Naturhistoriska Riksmuseet (Box 176). The colors of the vestiture are better preserved in the male than in the females. We interpret that all these specimens are 
<typeStatus id="7E4CD3C48C6CFFA6FE711A501F04C706" box="[500,583,859,880]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">syntypes</typeStatus>
of the series studied by 
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FCB51A501E92C706" author="Boheman" box="[816,977,859,880]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref3956" refString="Boheman, C. H. 1833 - 1845. In: Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae (C. J. Schoenherr). Roret, Paris, Fleischer, Lipsiae. Vols. 1 - 8." type="book chapter" year="1833">Boheman (1833)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FF411A7E1C3CC7FC" author="Schoenherr" box="[196,383,885,906]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 474" refId="ref4707" refString="Schoenherr, C. J. 1840. Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae. Roret, Paris, Fleischer, Lipsiae. Vol. 6, pt. 1, pp. I, 1 - 474." type="journal article" year="1840">Schoenherr (1840)</bibRefCitation>
. On the other hand, in the Schoenherr collection of the Naturhistoriska Riksmuseet (Box 14), there is 
<specimenCount id="B7F1A6EF8C6CFFA6FDDA1A9B1F89C7D3" box="[607,714,912,933]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" type="female">one female</specimenCount>
from 
<collectingCountry id="D9E02DF68C6CFFA6FC8F1A9B1E05C7D3" box="[778,838,912,933]" name="Brazil" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, with label of 
<typeStatus id="7E4CD3C48C6CFFA6FF111AA11DAAC7C9" box="[148,233,938,959]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">paratype</typeStatus>
. We are not sure if this is a true type, since in the original descriptions by Perty (1832) and 
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FE841ACE1CE1C7AC" author="Boheman" box="[257,418,965,986]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="1 - 8" refId="ref3956" refString="Boheman, C. H. 1833 - 1845. In: Genera et species curculionidum, cum synonymia hujus familiae (C. J. Schoenherr). Roret, Paris, Fleischer, Lipsiae. Vols. 1 - 8." type="book chapter" year="1833">Boheman (1833)</bibRefCitation>
there is not information on the designation of the 
<typeStatus id="7E4CD3C48C6CFFA6FCF81ACE1E93C7AC" box="[893,976,965,986]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">holotype</typeStatus>
and 
<typeStatus id="7E4CD3C48C6CFFA6FF381AD41C58C782" box="[189,283,991,1012]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52">paratypes</typeStatus>
. The type material studied by Perty (1832) should be at the Museum of Munich (
<bibRefCitation id="C56610978C6CFFA6FF691AF11C37C079" author="Kuschel" box="[236,372,1018,1039]" pageId="5" pageNumber="52" pagination="261 - 312" refId="ref4305" refString="Kuschel, G. 1955. Nuevas sinonimias y anotaciones sobre Curculionoidea (Coleoptera). Revista Chilena de Entomologia 4: 261 - 312." type="journal article" year="1955">Kuschel 1955</bibRefCitation>
) but we have not examined it.
</paragraph>
